001
002package gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.metapath.item.node;
003
004import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.model.IAssemblyDefinition;
005import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.model.IAssemblyInstance;
006import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.model.IAssemblyInstanceAbsolute;
007import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.model.IChoiceGroupInstance;
008import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.model.IChoiceInstance;
009import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.model.IContainerModelAbsolute;
010import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.model.IFieldDefinition;
011import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.model.IFieldInstance;
012import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.model.IFieldInstanceAbsolute;
013import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.model.IModelInstance;
014import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.model.IModule;
015import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.model.INamedModelInstance;
016import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.model.INamedModelInstanceAbsolute;
017import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.util.ObjectUtils;
018
019import java.net.URI;
020import java.util.stream.Stream;
021
022import javax.xml.namespace.QName;
023
024import edu.umd.cs.findbugs.annotations.NonNull;
025import edu.umd.cs.findbugs.annotations.Nullable;
026
027public abstract class AbstractNodeItemFactory implements INodeItemFactory, INodeItemGenerator {
028  @Override
029  public IDocumentNodeItem newDocumentNodeItem(
030      IAssemblyDefinition definition,
031      URI documentUri,
032      Object value) {
033    return new DocumentNodeItemImpl(
034        definition,
035        value,
036        documentUri,
037        this);
038  }
039
040  @Override
041  public IModuleNodeItem newModuleNodeItem(IModule module) {
042    return new ModuleNodeItemImpl(
043        module,
044        this);
045  }
046
047  @Override
048  public IFieldNodeItem newFieldNodeItem(
049      IFieldDefinition definition,
050      IModuleNodeItem module) {
051    return new FieldGlobalDefinitionNodeItemImpl(
052        definition,
053        module,
054        this);
055  }
056
057  @Override
058  public IFieldNodeItem newFieldNodeItem(
059      IFieldDefinition definition,
060      URI baseUri) {
061    return new FieldOrphanedDefinitionNodeItemImpl(
062        definition,
063        baseUri,
064        this);
065  }
066
067  @Override
068  public IFieldNodeItem newFieldNodeItem(
069      IFieldInstance instance,
070      IAssemblyNodeItem parent) {
071    return new FieldInstanceNoValueNodeItemImpl(instance, parent, this);
072  }
073
074  @Override
075  public IFieldNodeItem newFieldNodeItem(
076      IFieldInstance instance,
077      IAssemblyNodeItem parent,
078      int position,
079      Object value) {
080    return new FieldInstanceNodeItemImpl(instance, parent, position, value, this);
081  }
082
083  @Override
084  public IAssemblyNodeItem newAssemblyNodeItem(
085      IAssemblyDefinition definition,
086      IModuleNodeItem module) {
087    return new AssemblyGlobalDefinitionNodeItemImpl(
088        definition,
089        module,
090        this);
091  }
092
093  @Override
094  public IAssemblyNodeItem newAssemblyNodeItem(
095      IAssemblyDefinition definition,
096      URI baseUri) {
097    return new AssemblyOrphanedDefinitionNodeItemImpl(
098        definition,
099        baseUri,
100        this);
101  }
102
103  @Override
104  public IAssemblyNodeItem newAssemblyNodeItem(
105      IAssemblyDefinition definition,
106      URI baseUri,
107      Object value) {
108    return new AssemblyOrphanedDefinitionDataNodeItemImpl(
109        definition,
110        baseUri,
111        value,
112        this);
113  }
114
115  @Override
116  public IAssemblyNodeItem newAssemblyNodeItem(
117      IAssemblyInstance instance,
118      IAssemblyNodeItem parent) {
119    IAssemblyNodeItem retval = null;
120    if (!instance.getDefinition().isInline()) {
121      // if not inline, need to check for a cycle
122      IAssemblyNodeItem cycle = getCycledInstance(instance.getXmlQName(), instance.getDefinition(), parent);
123      if (cycle != null) {
124        // generate a cycle wrapper of the original node item
125        retval = new CycledAssemblyInstanceNodeItemImpl(instance, parent, cycle);
126      }
127    }
128
129    if (retval == null) {
130      retval = new AssemblyInstanceNoValueNodeItemImpl(instance, parent, this);
131    }
132    return retval;
133  }
134
135  @Override
136  public IAssemblyNodeItem newAssemblyNodeItem(
137      IAssemblyInstance instance,
138      IAssemblyNodeItem parent,
139      int position,
140      Object value) {
141    return new AssemblyInstanceNodeItemImpl(instance, parent, position, value, this);
142  }
143
144  @Nullable
145  private IAssemblyNodeItem getCycledInstance(
146      @NonNull QName name,
147      @NonNull IAssemblyDefinition definition,
148      @NonNull IAssemblyNodeItem parent) {
149    IAssemblyNodeItem retval = null;
150
151    IAssemblyDefinition parentDefinition = parent.getDefinition();
152    if (parent.getQName().equals(name) && parentDefinition.equals(definition)) {
153      retval = parent;
154    } else {
155      IAssemblyNodeItem ancestor = parent.getParentContentNodeItem();
156      if (ancestor != null) {
157        retval = getCycledInstance(name, definition, ancestor);
158      }
159    }
160    return retval;
161  }
162
163  /**
164   * Create a new {@link IModelNodeItem} based on the provided {@code instance}
165   * that is a child of the provided {@code parent}. This new item will have the
166   * provided {@code value}.
167   *
168   * @param instance
169   *          the model instance to create the node for
170   * @param parent
171   *          the item to use as the parent item for the created node item
172   * @param position
173   *          the data item's position in the sequence of data items for the
174   *          instance, which is {@code 0} based
175   * @param value
176   *          the data item's value
177   * @return the created node item
178   */
179  @NonNull
180  protected IModelNodeItem<?, ?> newModelItem(
181      @NonNull INamedModelInstance instance,
182      @NonNull IAssemblyNodeItem parent,
183      int position,
184      @NonNull Object value) {
185    @NonNull
186    IModelNodeItem<?, ?> item;
187    if (instance instanceof IAssemblyInstance) {
188      item = newAssemblyNodeItem((IAssemblyInstance) instance, parent, position, value);
189    } else if (instance instanceof IFieldInstance) {
190      item = newFieldNodeItem((IFieldInstance) instance, parent, position, value);
191    } else {
192      throw new UnsupportedOperationException("unsupported instance type: " + instance.getClass().getName());
193    }
194    return item;
195  }
196
197  /**
198   * Create a new {@link IModelNodeItem} based on the provided {@code instance}
199   * that is a child of the provided {@code parent}. This new item will have no
200   * associated value.
201   *
202   * @param instance
203   *          the model instance to create the node for
204   * @param parent
205   *          the item to use as the parent item for the created node item
206   * @return the created node item
207   */
208  @NonNull
209  protected IModelNodeItem<?, ?> newModelItem(
210      @NonNull INamedModelInstance instance,
211      @NonNull IAssemblyNodeItem parent) {
212    @NonNull
213    IModelNodeItem<?, ?> item;
214    if (instance instanceof IAssemblyInstance) {
215      item = newAssemblyNodeItem((IAssemblyInstance) instance, parent);
216    } else if (instance instanceof IFieldInstance) {
217      item = newFieldNodeItem((IFieldInstance) instance, parent);
218    } else {
219      throw new UnsupportedOperationException("unsupported instance type: " + instance.getClass().getName());
220    }
221    return item;
222  }
223
224  /**
225   * Get the descendant model instances of the provided {@code container}.
226   *
227   * @param container
228   *          the container to get descendant instances for
229   * @return the stream of descendant instances
230   */
231  @NonNull
232  protected Stream<? extends INamedModelInstance> getNamedModelInstances(@NonNull IContainerModelAbsolute container) {
233    return ObjectUtils.notNull(container.getModelInstances().stream()
234        .flatMap(instance -> {
235          Stream<? extends INamedModelInstance> retval;
236          if (instance instanceof IAssemblyInstanceAbsolute || instance instanceof IFieldInstanceAbsolute) {
237            retval = Stream.of((INamedModelInstanceAbsolute) instance);
238          } else if (instance instanceof IChoiceInstance) {
239            // descend into the choice
240            retval = getNamedModelInstances((IChoiceInstance) instance);
241          } else if (instance instanceof IChoiceGroupInstance) {
242            IChoiceGroupInstance choiceGroupInstance = (IChoiceGroupInstance) instance;
243            retval = choiceGroupInstance.getNamedModelInstances().stream();
244          } else {
245            throw new UnsupportedOperationException("unsupported instance type: " + instance.getClass().getName());
246          }
247          return retval;
248        }));
249  }
250
251  /**
252   * Get the descendant model instances of the provided {@code container}.
253   *
254   * @param container
255   *          the container to get descendant instances for
256   * @return the stream of descendant instances
257   */
258  @NonNull
259  protected Stream<? extends IModelInstance> getValuedModelInstances(@NonNull IContainerModelAbsolute container) {
260    return ObjectUtils.notNull(container.getModelInstances().stream()
261        .flatMap(instance -> {
262          Stream<? extends IModelInstance> retval;
263          if (instance instanceof IAssemblyInstanceAbsolute || instance instanceof IFieldInstanceAbsolute) {
264            retval = Stream.of((INamedModelInstanceAbsolute) instance);
265          } else if (instance instanceof IChoiceInstance) {
266            // descend into the choice
267            retval = getNamedModelInstances((IChoiceInstance) instance);
268          } else if (instance instanceof IChoiceGroupInstance) {
269            retval = Stream.of((IChoiceGroupInstance) instance);
270          } else {
271            throw new UnsupportedOperationException("unsupported instance type: " + instance.getClass().getName());
272          }
273          return retval;
274        }));
275  }
276}
